{-
  Finitely presented algebras.
  An R-algebra A is finitely presented, if there merely is an exact sequence
  of R-modules:

    (f₁,⋯,fₘ) → R[X₁,⋯,Xₙ] → A → 0

  (where f₁,⋯,fₘ ∈ R[X₁,⋯,Xₙ])
-}
